N2  - The article details a management policy course offered at Western Michigan University for business students, Management Problems 499. The core program aims to develop managerial skills such as systematic problem solving, appropriate role behavior, effective communication of ideas, and efficient allocation of resources. The policy course?developed by R. L. Wallace, H. K. Wilson, and J. M. Keenan?creates a symbiotic relationship between the university and business world by giving students an opportunity to apply management theory to real problems and to serve the community as consultants.
