N2  - The article discusses a conflict resolution model that is based on a power paradigm. The social power properties?which produce distinct influences and behavioral states that impact the outcome of organizational transactions?are dependency and availability of alternatives (A/A). Combinations of A/A and asymmetrical or symmetrical dependency balance (DB) are the power properties which lead to rebellious, dominant, docile, benevolent, competitive, or cooperative behavior states and result in the conflict resolution modes of suppression, submission, control, conformity, win/lose, coercive, and integrative/compromise.
